body( data-spy = "scroll", data-target = ".bs-docs-sidebar" )
  !{partial('includes/docs-nav.html')}
  
  header.jumbotron.subhead#overview
    div.container-px-width
      h2.bs-docs-heading Getting started
      p.p1
        | Overview of the project, its contents, and how to get started with a simple template.
  div.container-px-width
    div.grid
      div.span3.bs-docs-sidebar
        ul.simple-nav.simple-nav-list.bs-docs-sidenav
          li
            a(href='#download-bootstrap')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | Download
          li
            a(href='#file-structure')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | File structure
          li
            a(href='#contents')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | What's included
          li
            a(href='#html-template')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | HTML template
          li
            a(href='#examples')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | Examples
          li
            a(href='#what-next')
              i.icon-chevron-right
              | What next?
      div.span9
        section#download-bootstrap
          h2.bs-docs-heading 1. Download
          p.p1
            | Before downloading, be sure to have a code editor (we recommend 
            a(href='http://sublimetext.com/2') Sublime Text 2 
            | ) and some working knowledge of HTML and CSS. We won't walk through the source files here, but they are available for download. We'll focus on getting started with the compiled Bootstrap files.
          div.grid
            div.span6
              h3.bs-docs-heading Download compiled
              p
                strong Fastest way to get started:
                | get the compiled and minified versions of our CSS, JS, and images. No docs or original source files.
              p
                a.btn.btn-large.btn-special(href="bootstrap.zip", onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'Getting started', 'Download', 'Download compiled']);") Download Bootstrap
            div.span6
              h3.bs-docs-heading Download source
              p
                | Get the original files for all CSS and JavaScript, along with a local copy of the docs by downloading the latest version directly from GitHub.
              p
                a.btn.btn-large(href="https://github.com/twitter/bootstrap/zipball/master", onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'Getting started', 'Download', 'Download source']);") Download Bootstrap source
        section#file-structure
          h2.bs-docs-heading 2. File structure
          p.p1
            | Within the download you'll find the following file structure and contents, logically grouping common assets and providing both compiled and minified variations.
          p
            | Once downloaded, unzip the compressed folder to see the structure of (the compiled) Bootstrap. You'll see something like this:
          pre.prettyprint
            | bootstrap/
            | ├── css/
            | │   ├── bootstrap.css
            | │   ├── bootstrap.min.css
            | ├── js/
            | │   ├── bootstrap.js
            | │   ├── bootstrap.min.js
            | ├── img/
            | │   ├── glyphicons-halflings.png
            | │   ├── glyphicons-halflings-white.png
            | └── README.md
          p
            | This is the most basic form of Bootstrap: compiled files for quick drop-in usage in nearly any web project. We provide compiled CSS and JS (
            code
              | bootstrap.*
            | ), as well as compiled and minified CSS and JS (
            code
              | bootstrap.min.*
            | ). The image files are compressed using 
            a(href='http://imageoptim.com/') ImageOptim
            | , a Mac app for compressing PNGs.
          p
            | Please note that all JavaScript plugins require jQuery to be included.
        section#contents
          h2.bs-docs-heading 3. What's included
          p.p1
            | Bootstrap comes equipped with HTML, CSS, and JS for all sorts of things, but they can be summarized with a handful of categories visible at the top of the 
            a(href='http://getbootstrap.com') Bootstrap documentation
            | .
          h3.bs-docs-heading Docs sections
          h5.bs-docs-heading
            a(href='http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/scaffolding.html') Scaffolding
          p
            | Global styles for the body to reset type and background, link styles, grid system, and two simple layouts.
          h5.bs-docs-heading
            a(href='http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/base-css.html') Base CSS
          p
            | Styles for common HTML elements like typography, code, tables, forms, and buttons. Also includes 
            a(href='http://glyphicons.com') Glyphicons
            | , a great little icon set.
          h5.bs-docs-heading
            a(href='http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/components.html') Components
          p
            | Basic styles for common interface components like tabs and pills, navbar, alerts, page headers, and more.
          h5.bs-docs-heading
            a(href='http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/javascript.html') Javascript plugins
          p
            | Similar to Components, these Javascript plugins are interactive components for things like tooltips, popovers, modals, and more.
          h3.bs-docs-heading List of components
          p
            | Together, the
            strong Components
            | and
            strong Javascript plugins
            | sections provide the following interface elements:
          ul
            li
              | Button groups
            li
              | Button dropdowns
            li
              | Navigational tabs, pills, and lists
            li
              | Navbar
            li
              | Labels
            li
              | Badges
            li
              | Page headers and hero unit
            li
              | Thumbnails
            li
              | Alerts
            li
              | Progress bars
            li
              | Modals
            li
              | Dropdowns
            li
              | Tooltips
            li
              | Popovers
            li
              | Accordion
            li
              | Carousel
            li
              | Typeahead
          p
            | In future guides, we may walk through these components individually in more detail. Until then, look for each of these in the documentation for information on how to utilize and customize them.
        section#html-template
          h2.bs-docs-heading 4. Basic HTML template
          p.p1
            | With a brief intro into the contents out of the way, we can focus putting Bootstrap to use. To do that, we'll utilize a basic HTML template that includes everything we mentioned in the 
            a(href='#file-structure') File structure
            | .
          p
            | Now, here's a look at a
            strong typical HTML file
            | :
          pre.prettyprint.linenums
            | &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
            | &lt;html&gt;
            |   &lt;head&gt;
            |     &lt;title&gt;Bootstrap 101 Template&lt;/title&gt;
            |   &lt;/head&gt;
            |   &lt;body&gt;
            |     &lt;h1&gt;Hello, world!&lt;/h1&gt;
            |     &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            |   &lt;/body&gt;
            | &lt;/html&gt;
          p
            | To make this
            strong a Bootstrapped template
            | , just include the appropriate CSS and JS files:
          pre.prettyprint.linenums
            | &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
            | &lt;html&gt;
            |   &lt;head&gt;
            |     &lt;title&gt;Bootstrap 101 Template&lt;/title&gt;
            |     &lt;!-- Bootstrap --&gt;
            |     &lt;link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"&gt;
            |   &lt;/head&gt;
            |   &lt;body&gt;
            |     &lt;h1&gt;Hello, world!&lt;/h1&gt;
            |     &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            |     &lt;script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
            |   &lt;/body&gt;
            | &lt;/html&gt;
          p
            strong And you're set!
            | With those two files added, you can begin to develop any site or application with Bootstrap.
        section#examples
          h2.bs-docs-heading 5. Examples
          p.p1
            | Move beyond the base template with a few example layouts. We encourage folks to iterate on these examples and not simply use them as an end result.
          ul.thumbnails.bootstrap-examples
            li.span3
              a.thumbnail(href='examples/hero.html')
                img(src='img/examples/bootstrap-example-hero.jpg',alt='')
              h5.bs-docs-heading Basic marketing site
              p
                | Featuring a hero unit for a primary message and three supporting elements.
            li.span3
              a.thumbnail(href='examples/fluid.html')
                img(src='img/examples/bootstrap-example-fluid.jpg',alt='')
              h5.bs-docs-heading Fluid layout
              p
                | Uses our new responsive, fluid grid system to create a seamless liquid layout.
            li.span3
              a.thumbnail(href='examples/starter-template.html')
                img(src='img/examples/bootstrap-example-starter.jpg',alt='')
              h5.bs-docs-heading Starter template
              p
                | A barebones HTML document with all the Bootstrap CSS and javascript included.
        section#what-next
          h2.bs-docs-heading What next?
          p.p1
            | Head to the docs for information, examples, and code snippets, or take the next leap and customize Bootstrap for any upcoming project.
          a.btn.btn-large.btn-special(href="./scaffolding.html", onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'Getting started', 'Next steps', 'Visit docs']);") Visit the Bootstrap docs 
          a.btn.btn-large(href="./customize.html", style="margin-left: 5px;", onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'Getting started', 'Next steps', 'Customize']);") Customize Bootstrap
